13. Failure Modes

False neutrality

Pretending the baseline has no weighting.

Source laundering

Repeated citation chains that appear diverse but are not.

Overcompression

Summaries that erase uncertainty.

Hidden ideology

Bias hiding inside extraction rules instead of visible profiles.

Engagement corruption

Optimizing for clicks instead of truth legibility.

Speculation bleed

Predictions presented as facts.

